im switching journals because this one got kinda screwed up when livejournal had all those problems. so instead of bitch about it waiting for somehting to happen i made a new one. its cool, im just wondering how do you delete a journal? i think ive seen people do it... if not just tell me to shut up and that im an idiot.

only i messed up when i signed up for it. i forgot the p in sPhincter. but oh well, you get it. if not, ill educate you. just ask.

im doing so much better this year so far. im staying on top of my homework and studying alot. it feels good but sometimes there is the feeling that it is a little too late. i dont know why, i only did bad in 2 classes in my whole high school career everything else is a's and b's. not to mention ive never taken a regular class if an honors one was offered. ive already got college credit under my belt and more coming soon... so why am i still so worried?
today i put in my application for Florida State. i almost got my bright futures application done but my computer kept freezing so im gonna do it tomorrow.
i have to get my physical papers in tomorrow, i have an appointment at 245 so im gonna ask the office ladies if i can fax it or if they can wait for me to come back... it shouldnt take long. 
softball is going to be interesting, i think the fact that i am one of the only seniors going out for it and the fact that all of the coaches know me personally and know that whatever i lack in phenomenal talent i make up for in dedication, leadership, and team building skills. coach parker said im a solid player and that i have an assured spot on varsity as long as i havent forgotten how to play... yea right, me forget the love of my life... i dont think so.
im so happy that i wrecked my car right now.
even tho it is difficult to find people kind enough to pay me back for all the times i gave them rides to and from places WAY out of my way i think it is becoming one of those blessing in disguise because im able to do things i wasnt able to do. and i find that i am doing more of the things i should be doing...

my mom says that if i make straight a's she is going to give me 5 thousand dollars towards a car and allow me to use her credit to buy a new used one. im thinking honda civic or something along those lines. unless i find my jeep CJ7 in good condition. im sure i will, and then i will be riding in style up in tallahassee. im starting to agree with those who say, "good things come to those who wait..." well here i am, patiently awaiting my reward for working hard, and i see it in my near future. it looks goooooooooood.

no more mark = no more stress
no more stress = happy lindsey
happy lindsey = happy mommy
happy mommy = car for lindsey
car for lindsey = happy lindsey
happy lindsey = an increasing opportunity cost... lol, just kidding. economics on the brain

chew on this one bible thumpers;

Frightful must it be; for supremely frightful would be the effect of any human endeavour to mock the stupendous mechanism of the Creator of the world. His success would terrify the artist; he would rush away from his odious handywork, horror-stricken. He would hope that left to itself, the slight spark of life which he had communicated would fade; that this thing, which had received such imperfect animation, would subside into dead matter; and he might sleep in the belief that the silence of the grave would quench for ever the transient existence of the hideous corpse which he had looked upon as the cradle of life. He sleeps.

accidents of life. what if we were an accident; or a miscalculation. what if the reason we cant find any other life and why no other form of life is willing to approach us is because we are a time bomb. if we know that our actions are going to ultimately end in our termination why do we continue on the same path? isnt total annihilation a good incentive to take another route... or to make a drastic change? here we are, floating in nothing, made of everything, and destroying all that we touch. conveinantly trapped by our surroundings and the simple fact that we will destroy ourselves. what do police do to a bomb they cant stop? they isolate it and make sure that when it goes off it doesnt damage or endanger anything else.

what if god realized his mistake? what if we were the frankenstein of his creations? if he knew that we were hazardous to all the others he created dont you think he would protect them from us? we are parasites. ok look at it this way. the earth is a host. in a symbiotic relationship the earth and humans would have to mutually benefit from each other.... or just coexist in harmony. so what do you call the relation ship of the earth and the humans that are slowly destroying her, sucking her resources dry and planning on moving on to another host. why do you think they are pushing nasa to make it to other planets... to land people on other worlds? we want to destroy this host and move on to another, just like a virus. we are equivalent to a stellar flu. seek and destroy. there's no logic in it. eventually we run out of resources and have no more hosts to depend on.

when you think about it, we are worse than parasites. parasites have no reasoning capabilities, they are like machines and only do what instinct tells them too. we have the ability to change and evolve. we have developed ways to help save the earth. but our own nature destroys any hopes of this taking place. which is more important? living or having money. life or power? humanity or social status?

im disgusted.

My name represents me accurately in all of my complexity. Lindsey means "a Linden tree by the water" according to Old English. At first I was frustrated by the simplicity of the meaning of my name. I wanted a mysterious name, a romantic one full of meaning like "exalted" or "holy" or "powerful." As I started to think about trees and what could be so exciting about a tree by the water, I realized that no other name would better symbolize all that I am. A tree is a living paradox full of symbology. Conflicts of thoughts and emotions are embedded in the image of the tree. The roots of the tree bury deep into tradition and family, taking comfort in the warm shelter of the ground; perfect stability. The branches and leaves, at the other end, reach out, forever searching, growing, and changing; thirsting ambition. The tree never moves, yet re-invents itself in a constant cycle. The seasons accent various qualities hidden within the tree. In the winter, the tree loses its leaves. It becomes ugly and naked; vunerable. It looks dead, lost and forgotten. As spring melts away winter, the tree blossoms and explodes with happiness, life and beauty. Vitality and valiance radiate around the tree and infect those closest to it. Summer is the unpredictability of life. Long droughts and torential downpours can happen back to back. Hurricanes and firestorms rage unchecked. Beautiful sunny days full of laughter and play scatter themselves amoung the moments of madness. Fall forshadows winter but comes with its own set of emotions. Resilliance and flexibility are most apparent as it prepares itself for the long cold winter. Sometimes, if you look hard enough, the radical colors can reveal just a glimpse into the attitude and drive that keeps the tree's will to survive afloat and its heart beating.

but it got pretty heated and i went to my room to avoid it.

i think my mom and mark got into a pretty big argument after that because she came barging into my room asking for her keys... i had them because i didnt want her driving any where, i told her i didnt know where they were. she got pissed and start demanding her keys. i called philip and had him come get me. my mom said that she wanted to drive down to Boca Raton to see my godmother that night so i took the keys with me just to be sure she wouidnt. i called to check on her an hour later. she was still at home but she was packing to HITCHHIKE DOWN TO BOCA!!! i freaked out and had philip drive me home to stop her. i called my brother and he got on his way over.

when i got there we got into an argument about none other than my tongue ring... i was so pissed that she thought that my priorities were screwed and that i took her keys to be a bitch and to get attention that i took the damn thing out and threw it on the ground.... NOTHING CHANGED... SHE WAS STILL PISSED AND DIDNT EVEN SAY ANYTHING ABOUT ME TAKING IT OUT. so i put the damn thing back in and tried to leave. she blocked the door, GRABBED THE HOOD OF MY JACKET AND THREW ME IN THE BATHROOM. THEN SHE THREW ME AGAINST THE WALL CALLING ME BITCH AND SLUT. i tried to get out of the bathroom.... but i couldnt so i called 911. i talked to the operator and got my mom to talk to her. as my mom was distracted i nudged her off the door and almost got out. after she realized what i was doing SHE PUSHED HERSELF UP AGAINST THE DOOR TO KEEP ME FROM LEAVING AND SHE FELL BACKWARDS OUT OF THE BATHROOM AND FELL ON HER BACK. SHE GOT UP AND GRABBED ME CALLING ME BITCH AND HITTING ME SWINGING ME AROUND AND THREW ME ON THE BED AND STARTED TO HIT ME.

philip finally got past mark (WHO AT THE TIME OF ALL THIS WAS SITTING THERE MAKING FUN OF MY SCREAMING, MOCKING ME AND LAUGHING... SICK TWISTED FUCK) and philip pulled my mom off of me. i got out of the house. mark tried to call the cops to say that philip was intruding in our house but i had already called the cops so that wasnt flying. we drove down the street to get away from mark and my mom and waited for the cops.

when they got there i told them everything and they collected statements from me, philip and my step father. my brother finally got there, and he was by my mother's side the whole time. the cops escorted me back into the house to get some clothes so i could stay the night with philip. 

so as of now, i dont have family because my brother said i fucked up. he says he doesnt care if mother is holding a knife to my throat... i NEVER call the cops on mom. he said that if she goes to jail for this (which i dont want... i want a restraining order against mark) that he will disown me forever. when i told him i wanted to move out and go away forever he got up and went to punch me and said "IF YOU WERENT MY SISTER I WOULD PUNCH THE FUCK OUT OF YOUR FACE YOU SELFISH BITCH."

i want to die. i really do. i dont know where to go or what to do. i am so lost, and i dont see a way out of it. death.

wow, that was awesome. ok here's a recap of all the excitement... trust me, you'll want to read it. just hang in there, the last day is hilarious.

thursday- woke up at 2AM... ouch. left the house at 3 and boarded our plane at 6AM. sat by the window and had a blast. there was a one hour layover in memphis tennisee. HAHAHA COWBOYS EVERYWHERE! boarded another plane, once again next to a window having a good ole time. finally arrive in denver at 10 am (there's a 2 hour time difference so when added up i spent 6 hours in the air.) met my aunt and got a rental car. drove out to boulder colorado and had a campus tour. beautiful campus... absolutely gorgeous... but they were pretty snobby and i definately did not feel welcome at the University of Colorado so screw em. after that we got lunch and headed for my aunts house, after i got there i crashed and hit the hay cause i had been awake for 21 hours... damn jet lag. zzzzzzzz

friday- woke up at 530AM. my aunt drove us to boulder again to meet with the horn professor for a free lesson. yea, he was a jerk screw him. what an ass. after that we drove to fort collins to visit Colorado State University. AWESOMENESS!!! a little more modern than CU. and definately friendlier. i got a free dvd, video and cd from the drum major and coordinator of bands. both of them sat down with me and answered all my questions, they were awesome. they even went and got the mello section leader to talk to me about specifics and stuff... awesome. went on a campus tour, saw the dorms and the student union and everything. i got to see a class in session and the i met with the liberal arts advisor... HE WAS AWESOME!!! cant remember his name tho. so ive made up my mind... well sort of. fuck majoring in music... there's no point. im gonna go into liberal arts as an open option student and figure it out from there. yea its awesome. after that we got lunch and headed home to my aunts. we hung out and went to sleep. zzzzzzz

saturday- woke up at 6AM and drove 2 hours to Winter Park ski resort. got my ass WHOOPED. man, colorado snow is so different from east coast snow. way more powder than im used to. i wiped out so bad!!! I TOOK OUT A GODDAMN FENCE FOR CRYIN OUT LOUD! and i was only on a blue course! the runs are longer and steeper out there. i got the hang of it a little later... if i were to stay for a week i'd be ownin those slopes. that was some serious skiing. no one snowblades over there! i was the only one on the slopes that day with snowblades on. i felt like an outsider. but it was fun all the same. after that we drove home and went to a gingerbread house making party for my little cousins. too much icing,  my stomach was killing me. man, that was fun... too many kids. then i went to bed zzzzzzzz

sunday- woke up at 730 (woohoo, finally some rest) opened my belated birthday card and christmas card... i got 85 dollars in total!! woop woop! people are getting christmas gifts after all. tell me what ya want guys! then we packed and headed for the airport. first flight was alright, sat next to some cool chicks and got some sleep. after the layover in memphis i got stuck next to this middle eastern family that smelled so bad!!! HOLY CRAP I ALMOST PUKED SERIOUSLY. and to add on top of the smell, they had a screaming 3 year old spoiled brat that wouldnt shut up. so that was the flight from hell.

so now im home and i have to go to school tomorrow which suks so ill seeyou people tomorrow. dont expect me to move very quickly because my whole body is killing me. ouch. laters
